# Make AAO App Installable (PWA)

This implementation plan details the steps to convert the Antigravity Architect Orchestrator (AAO) into an installable Progressive Web App (PWA) that functions seamlessly on Desktop, iOS, and Android.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The image generator is currently out of capacity. As a fallback, I will hand-craft a sleek SVG icon representing the "AAO" brand. Chrome and Android natively support SVG app icons (`sizes="any"`). iOS usually requires PNGs, but for the sake of immediate deployment, we will use the generated App Router `icon.tsx` and `apple-icon.tsx` files which automatically generate optimized PNG icons on the fly via Next.js `ImageResponse` APIs.
> Let me know if you approve this approach!

## Proposed Changes

### PWA Assets (Public Directory)

#### [NEW] `public/sw.js`
A standard Service Worker script. We will implement a "Network First, falling back to cache" strategy to ensure dynamic pages (like the dashboard) always reflect the latest data, while fulfilling the browser requirement to have a registered `fetch` handler for installability.

#### [NEW] `public/manifest.json`
The Web App Manifest file defining how the application appears upon installation:
- **name**: "Antigravity Architect Orchestrator"
- **short_name**: "AAO v2"
- **display**: "standalone" (hides the browser UI)
- **theme_color / background_color**: `#0a0a0a` (Midnight aesthetic)

### Application Configuration (App Router)

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/layout.tsx`
- Add a new `export const viewport` variable for `themeColor` and `viewport` configurations.
- Update the `metadata` object to include the `manifest`, `appleWebApp` capabilities (fullscreen status bar style, title), and `applicationName`.

#### [NEW] `src/components/PwaRegistry.tsx`
A client component (`"use client"`) utilizing `useEffect` to safely register the `/sw.js` service worker upon initialization without interfering with SSR flows.

#### [NEW] `src/app/icon.tsx` / `src/app/apple-icon.tsx`
Dynamic icon generation via `next/og` (`ImageResponse`). These endpoints will guarantee that robust pixel-perfect Android (192, 512, etc.) and Apple Touch (180x180) icon formats are provided without the need to manage static image files manually.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Execute `npm run build` to verify all route and icon generation dependencies correctly complete.
- Launch the `npm run dev` server.
- Verify via Chrome DevTools (**Application > Manifest** & **Service Workers** tabs) that the site indicates it is installable.
- (User) Opening the localhost URL on Safari (iOS Simulator) and tapping "Add to Home Screen" to see the custom dark 'AAO' generated icon.
